<subSubSection id="FDAA651F06012E4DFF48FDB9FD8C240B" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B50F369406012E4DFF48FDB9FD8C240B" blockId="43.[151,1437,150,1149]" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFF48FDB9FEA825FA" bold="true" box="[199,322,150,176]" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Carapace longer than wide, oblong-shaped; evenly convex; branchial groove shallow; short dense tomentum; rostrum short, tridentate, median tooth small not visible dorsally; strong supraorbital and suborbital teeth; concave area immediately behind orbit shelf-like; anterolateral margin beginning at orbital level, without teeth. Cheliped without epipod. Female thoracic sternal sutures 7/8 ending together on central raised ridge between bases of P2, apertures directed anteriorly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FDAA651F06012E4DFF48FC64FF0C215B" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B50F369406012E4DFF48FC64FF0C215B" blockId="43.[151,1437,150,1149]" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFF48FC64FED1242F" bold="true" box="[199,315,331,357]" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFECCFC64FDBD242F" baseAuthorityName="Ruppell" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[323,599,331,357]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Lewindromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unidentata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFECCFC64FDBD242F" box="[323,599,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Lewindromia unidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="CDA7760406012E4DFCE3FC64FC39242F" box="[876,979,331,357]" name="Australia" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Australia</collectingCountry>
as 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFC75FC64FE8B24C3" authority="Campbell &amp; Stephenson, 1970" authorityName="Campbell &amp; Stephenson" authorityYear="1970" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Cryptodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unilobata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFC75FC64FAE0242F" box="[1018,1290,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Cryptodromia unilobata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B6506012E4DFA9DFC64FE8B24C3" author="Campbell, B. M. &amp; Stephenson, W." pageId="43" pageNumber="344" pagination="235 - 301" refId="ref25152" refString="Campbell, B. M. &amp; Stephenson, W. (1970) The sublittoral Brachyura (Crustacea: Decapoda) of Moreton Bay. Memoirs of the Queensland Museum, 15, 235 - 301." type="journal article" year="1970">Campbell &amp; Stephenson, 1970</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, having been found in Moreton Bay 
<collectingRegion id="7774F87606012E4DFD79FC40FC9424C3" box="[758,894,367,393]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Queensland</collectingRegion>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B6506012E4DFC08FC40FB7524C3" author="Guinot, D. &amp; Tavares, M." box="[903,1183,367,393]" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" pagination="43 - 129" refId="ref26035" refString="Guinot, D. &amp; Tavares, M. (2003) A new subfamilial arrangement for the Dromiidae de Haan, 1833, with diagnoses and descriptions of new genera and species (Crustacea, Decapoda, Brachyura). Zoosystema, 25, 43 - 129." type="journal article" year="2003">Guinot &amp; Tavares (2003)</bibRefCitation>
erected the monotypic genus 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFF6FFCBCFE9E24E7" authorityName="Guinot &amp; Tavares" authorityYear="2003" box="[224,372,403,429]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Lewindromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFF6FFCBCFE9E24E7" box="[224,372,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Lewindromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to accommodate 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFDB3FCBCFC5124E7" authority="Ruppell, 1830" authorityName="Ruppell" authorityYear="1830" box="[572,955,403,429]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Dromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unidentata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFDB3FCBCFCFB24E7" box="[572,785,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Dromia unidentata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B6506012E4DFC97FCBCFC5124E7" author="Ruppell, E. W." box="[792,955,403,429]" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" pagination="3 - 28" refId="ref29730" refString="Ruppell, E. W. (1830) Beschreibung und Abbildung von 24 Arten kurzschwanzigen Krabben, als Beitrag zur Naturgeschichte des rothen Meeres. H. L. Bronner, Frankfurt, pp. 3 - 28." type="book chapter" year="1830">Rüppell, 1830</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, because it has several distinctive features. They compared 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFEDFFC98FE0D249B" authorityName="Ruppell" authorityYear="1830" box="[336,487,439,465]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Dromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unidentata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFEDFFC98FE0D249B" box="[336,487,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">L. unidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with several sponge carrying genera, but it is more constructive to compare it with species that have an intimate association with ascidians, such as 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFCF7FCF4FB5424BF" authority="Richters, 1880" authorityName="Richters" authorityYear="1880" box="[888,1214,475,501]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Ascidiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFCF7FCF4FBFA24BF" box="[888,1040,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Ascidiophilus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B6506012E4DFB96FCF4FB5424BF" author="Richters, F." box="[1049,1214,475,501]" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" pagination="139 - 178" refId="ref29687" refString="Richters, F. (1880) Decapoda. In: Mobius, L. (Ed.), Beitrage zur Meeresfauna der Insel Mauritius und der Seychellen. Mit Unterstutzung der Konigl, Akademie der Wissenschaften, 139 - 178." type="book chapter" year="1880">Richters, 1880</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
because 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFAA7FCF4FF292752" authorityName="Ruppell" authorityYear="1830" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Dromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unidentata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFAA7FCF4FF292752" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">L. unidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
often uses ascidians and soft corals for shelter. The life style of 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFC10FCD0FA762753" authority="Richters, 1880" authorityName="Richters" authorityYear="1880" box="[927,1436,511,537]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Ascidiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caphyraeformis">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFC10FCD0FB1A2753" box="[927,1264,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Ascidiophilus caphyraeformis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B6506012E4DFB77FCD0FA762753" author="Richters, F." box="[1272,1436,511,537]" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" pagination="139 - 178" refId="ref29687" refString="Richters, F. (1880) Decapoda. In: Mobius, L. (Ed.), Beitrage zur Meeresfauna der Insel Mauritius und der Seychellen. Mit Unterstutzung der Konigl, Akademie der Wissenschaften, 139 - 178." type="book chapter" year="1880">Richters, 1880</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is described by 
<bibRefCitation id="D1214B6506012E4DFEC6FF0CFE1E2777" author="Gordon, I." box="[329,500,546,573]" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" pagination="201 - 253" refId="ref25840" refString="Gordon, I. (1950) Crustacea: Dromiacea Part 1. Systematic account of the Dromiacea Collected by the &quot; John Murray &quot; Expedition. Part II. The Morphology of the spermatheca in certain Dromiacea. John Murray Expedition 1933 - 34 Scientific Reports, 9, 201 - 253." type="journal article" year="1950">Gordon (1950)</bibRefCitation>
. This species lives almost totally enclosed in an ascidian or other soft-bodied host. 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFF18FF68FE41272B" baseAuthorityName="Ruppell" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[151,427,583,609]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Lewindromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unidentata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFF18FF68FE41272B" box="[151,427,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Lewindromia unidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an elongate body with a smooth surface, long P5 to carry its host and female thoracic sternal grooves ending close together between the P2s as found in 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFC1FFF44FB8B27CF" authorityName="Richters" authorityYear="1880" box="[912,1121,619,645]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Ascidiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caphyraeformis">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFC1FFF44FB8B27CF" box="[912,1121,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">A. caphyraeformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, in 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFA8BFF44FEAD27E3" authorityName="Richters" authorityYear="1880" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Ascidiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caphyraeformis">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFA8BFF44FEAD27E3" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Ascidiophilus caphyraeformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the rostrum is strongly projecting forming a triangular extension, entire and supported beneath by a keel, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFEE7FF9CFE142787" baseAuthorityName="Ruppell" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[360,510,691,717]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Lewindromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unidentata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFEE7FF9CFE142787" box="[360,510,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">L. unidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is weakly tridentate, a condition more typical of sponge-carrying dromiid crabs. In 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFF39FFF8FE6F27BB" authorityName="Richters" authorityYear="1880" box="[182,389,727,753]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Ascidiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caphyraeformis">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFF39FFF8FE6F27BB" box="[182,389,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">A. caphyraeformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the rostrum and superior orbital border are continuous whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFBFCFFF8FAE327BB" baseAuthorityName="Ruppell" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[1139,1289,727,753]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Lewindromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unidentata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFBFCFFF8FAE327BB" box="[1139,1289,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">L. unidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the border is interrupted by a blunt preorbital tooth. In 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFDFBFFD4FCAF265F" authorityName="Richters" authorityYear="1880" box="[628,837,763,789]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Ascidiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caphyraeformis">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFDFBFFD4FCAF265F" box="[628,837,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">A. caphyraeformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the orbits are exposed, but in 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFB2DFFD4FAD3265F" baseAuthorityName="Ruppell" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[1186,1337,763,789]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Lewindromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unidentata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFB2DFFD4FAD3265F" box="[1186,1337,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">L. unidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are protected and have a suborbital tooth. The body shape also differs: in 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFC3AFE30FB6C2673" authorityName="Richters" authorityYear="1880" box="[949,1158,799,825]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Ascidiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caphyraeformis">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFC3AFE30FB6C2673" box="[949,1158,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">A. caphyraeformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the body is divided into 2 unequal sections by deep branchial grooves whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFCBDFE6CFC212617" baseAuthorityName="Ruppell" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[818,971,835,861]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Lewindromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unidentata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFCBDFE6CFC212617" box="[818,971,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">L. unidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
these grooves are much weaker and the carapace is more or less ovoid in shape. In 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFD0FFE48FCFC26CB" baseAuthorityName="Ruppell" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[640,790,871,897]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Lewindromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unidentata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFD0FFE48FCFC26CB" box="[640,790,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">L. unidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
uropods are present as dorsal plates (concealed) whereas they are absent in 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFEE4FEA4FDD626EF" authorityName="Richters" authorityYear="1880" box="[363,572,907,933]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Ascidiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caphyraeformis">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFEE4FEA4FDD626EF" box="[363,572,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">A. caphyraeformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFDC3FEA4FC8826EF" baseAuthorityName="Ruppell" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[588,866,907,933]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Lewindromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unidentata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFDC3FEA4FC8826EF" box="[588,866,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Lewindromia unidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a very hirsute body, densely covered by long setae, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFECFFE80FDFA2683" authorityName="Richters" authorityYear="1880" box="[320,528,943,969]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Ascidiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caphyraeformis">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFECFFE80FDFA2683" box="[320,528,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">A. caphyraeformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only has a short tomentum. In many respects the morphology of 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFB62FE80FA692683" baseAuthorityName="Ruppell" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[1261,1411,943,969]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Lewindromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unidentata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFB62FE80FA692683" box="[1261,1411,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">L. unidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is intermediate between the sponge-carrying habit and more specialized ascidian-carrying habit found in 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFA83FEFCFF35215B" authorityName="Richters" authorityYear="1880" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Ascidiophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caphyraeformis">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFA83FEFCFF35215B" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">A. caphyraeformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FDAA651F06012E4DFF48F935FCA22137" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B50F369406012E4DFF48F935FCA22137" blockId="43.[151,1437,150,1149]" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFF48F935FE8B217E" bold="true" box="[199,353,1050,1076]" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Distribution.</emphasis>
Red Sea, Indian Ocean, 
<collectingCountry id="CDA7760406012E4DFDF3F934FD1A217F" box="[636,752,1051,1077]" name="Singapore" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Singapore</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="CDA7760406012E4DFD73F934FCD5217F" box="[764,831,1051,1077]" name="Japan" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="CDA7760406012E4DFCC4F934FC26217F" box="[843,972,1051,1077]" name="Philippines" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, Queensland, 
<collectingCountry id="CDA7760406012E4DFBE3F934FAF7217F" box="[1132,1309,1051,1077]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
, Kermadec Islands (
<collectingCountry id="CDA7760406012E4DFF7BF910FE7A2110" box="[244,400,1087,1114]" name="New Zealand" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
), 
<collectingCountry id="CDA7760406012E4DFE2EF910FE032113" box="[417,489,1087,1113]" name="Tonga" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">Tonga</collectingCountry>
, Hawaii and Easter Island. The present specimen represents a new record for Western Australia. Depth range of 
<taxonomicName id="72B04D1706012E4DFE34F94CFDBA2137" baseAuthorityName="Ruppell" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[443,592,1123,1149]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dromiidae" genus="Lewindromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unidentata">
<emphasis id="87C4EA8606012E4DFE34F94CFDBA2137" box="[443,592,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="344">L. unidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is intertidal to 
<specimenCount id="A3B6FD1D06012E4DFD75F94CFCA22137" box="[762,840,1123,1149]" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" type="generic">
<quantity id="72489B7106012E4DFD75F94CFCAE2137" box="[762,836,1123,1149]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="43" pageNumber="344" unit="m" value="100.0">100 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
